title: Beautiful two bedroom lower level duplex in St Paul
posting_body: ["Kari Anderson and REI Real Estate & Property Management are happy to present this gorgeous two-bedroom, one-bathroom duplex in St. Paul's beautiful Summit Hill neighborhood.", 'The duplex has nearly 1,400 square feet of living space and it is located on the lower level of the home.', 'When you walk into the front, you will be in the living room.', 'It is a huge room that features stunning hardwood floors, a lovely decorative fireplace, lots of space and also a bunch of windows for natural light.', 'The living room runs into the dining room where you will find the same beautiful floors along with some built-in cabinetry.', 'Beyond the dining room is the kitchen and a spacious sunroom.', 'The kitchen has been completely remodeled and has tons of cabinets, matching appliances and modern colors.', 'The sunroom can be used year-round as an office, den, playroom or whatever you would like.', 'There are two bedrooms that are nice-sized and the bathroom is located between the bedrooms so the bedrooms do not share a wall.', 'Within a short distance of this duplex, you will find a lot of parks, recreation centers, school options, shopping destinations and restaurants.', 'It is also conveniently located by Highway 35E. Pets will be considered, but there are breed and size restrictions and there will be a pet deposit required.', 'The apartment has its own storage area in the basement along with its own laundry and extra fridge.', 'The backyard is huge and it offers patio space for entertaining and off-street parking as well.', 'The yard space is shared with the upper-level tenant and is completely fenced in.', 'The tenant is responsible for electricity, heat and trash.', 'Water is covered with the rent.', 'The lower-level tenant is responsible for snow removal.', 'Please call or text Kari Anderson at', 'show contact info', 'if you have any questions or if you would like to request a showing.', 'For help finding tenants or managing your property in the Twin Cities, see <URL>.']
